cer/internals/Sender.java:856)**: Iterates through drained batches and calls sendProduceRequest() for each node.\n\n9. **Sender.sendProduceRequest() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:864)**: Constructs a ProduceRequest from the batches, creates a ClientRequest, and calls client.send() to send the request.\n\n10. **NetworkClient.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java:541)**: Delegates to doSend() to handle protocol versioning and request serialization.\n\n11. **NetworkClient.doSend() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java:601)**: Serializes the request, creates an InFlightRequest, and calls selector.send() to queue the serialized data for network transmission.\n\n12. **Selector.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/network/Selector.java:391)**: Places the NetworkSend into a KafkaChannel queue, which will be transmitted over the socket during the next poll() cycle."
